cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.DC 

This paper presents a source-to-source compiler for JavaScript that extends its functionality with debugging abstractions and blocking operations. It also develops a Web IDE that supports stopping, single-stepping, breakpointing, and long-running computations. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL), Software Engineering (cs.SE), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, since the paper deals with improving the performance of JavaScript compilers, it may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories.
